COUNTESS It hath happened all as I would have had it, save that he comes not along with her. 

FOOL By my troth, I take my young lord to be a very melancholy man. 

COUNTESS By what observance, I pray you?	 

FOOL Why, he will look upon his boot and sing, mend the ruff and sing, ask questions and sing, pick his teeth and sing. I know a man that had this trick of melancholy sold a goodly manor for a song. 

COUNTESS Let me see what he writes and when he	 means to come.	She opens the letter. 

FOOL I have no mind to Isbel since I was at court. Our old lings and our Isbels o’ th’ country are nothing like your old ling and your Isbels o’ th’ court. The brains of my Cupid’s knocked out, and I begin to	 love as an old man loves money, with no stomach. 

COUNTESS What have we here? 

FOOL E’en that you have there.	 

